<devicedata>
    <copyright>Copyright 2015 Control4 Corporation. All rights reserved.</copyright>
    <config>
    <documentation>DriverWorks driver for the Control4 Mini Remote (IMR10A) Version 2.0 \n\nFEATURES:\n\nThe buttons on the Control4 Mini Remote are available for direct binding in the same fashion as Control4 LED Keypad buttons.\n\n\nINSTALLATION INSTRUCTIONS:\n\n     1. We suggest you assign the Mini Remote to a room in the home. You may also wish to place it adjacent to the devices you intend for it to control, although exact placement is not critical to functionality.\n\n     2. If desired, configure the LED color under the "Properties" tab. You must click "Set" for the properties to be applied.\n\n     3. To use the button-binding feature, go to the "Connections" tab and select the Control4 Mini Remote. Select the desired Button Link and drag it down to the appropiate output device listed in the bottom pane.\n\n     5. Use the "Programming" tab to program any other actions you would like to trigger based on button press, tap, hold, and release events for each button.\n\n     Button Press Event: Command is sent on initial press of the button.\n\n     Button Release Event: Command is sent when button is released.\n\n     Button Tap Event: Command is sent when button is released only if the button is held for less than .5 seconds.\n\n     Button Hold Event: Command is sent after the button has been held down for more than .5 seconds.\n\n    The Tap and Hold Events allow two functions to be performed by a single button. (Example: Toggle light with the Tap Event, and ramp dimmer on the Hold Event).\n\n
    </documentation>
    <identify_text>Press the large bottom button (button 5) on the Mini Remote four (4) times.</identify_text>
    <properties>
        <property>
            <name>Device Status</name>
            <type>STRING</type>
            <default>Not addressed</default>
            <readonly>true</readonly>
        </property>
        <property>
            <name>Battery Level</name>
            <type>STRING</type>
            <default>---</default>
            <readonly>true</readonly>
        </property>
        <property>
            <name>LED Color (Custom)</name>
            <type>STRING</type>
            <default>FF0000</default>
            <readonly>false</readonly>
        </property>
        <property>
            <name>LED Color (Standard)</name>
            <type>LIST</type>
            <items>
                <item>Custom</item>
                <item>Red</item>
                <item>Green</item>
                <item>Yellow</item>
                <item>Blue</item>
                <item>Magenta</item>
                <item>Cyan</item>
                <item>White</item>
                <item>Dim Red</item>
                <item>Dim Green</item>
                <item>Dim Yellow</item>
                <item>Dim Blue</item>
                <item>Dim Magenta</item>
                <item>Dim Cyan</item>
                <item>Dim White</item>
                <item>LED Off</item>
            </items>
            <default>Blue</default>
            <readonly>false</readonly>
        </property>
        <property>
            <name>Reflash Status</name>
            <type>STRING</type>
            <default>Reflash Idle</default>
            <readonly>true</readonly>
        </property>
        <property>
            <name>Debug Mode</name>
            <type>LIST</type>
            <items>
                <item>Off</item>
                <item>Print</item>
                <item>Log</item>
                <item>Print and Log</item>
            </items>
            <default>Off</default>
            <readonly>false</readonly>
        </property>
    </properties>
